1. Linear Regression
What it is: Predicts a number (output) based on input values. Imagine drawing the best straight line through data points.
Real-life Example: Predicting your score based on hours you study.

Code Example:
python
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
X = [[2], [4], [6], [8]]  # study hours
y = [60, 70, 80, 90]      # scores
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)
print(model.predict([[5]]))  # Predict score for 5 hours

Diagram:
text
(X)------*
    \
     *------ Best Fit Line ------*
